# Cyberland — Code Style and Comments

Code should be easy to follow for someone new to the file: **clear names first**, comments where they teach **why** and **how pieces connect**.

## Tutorial-style comments

- At the top of non-trivial modules, a short note on **purpose** and **main data flow** (a few lines).
- Before non-obvious logic: explain **intent**, **invariants**, and **edge cases**—not a restatement of the syntax.
- For performance-sensitive or size-sensitive code, tie comments to project goals (e.g. why this avoids extra copies or allocations).

## Readability

- Prefer small functions with one obvious job; extract when nesting or duplication hurts scanning.
- Use consistent naming for game concepts (systems, resources, entities) once chosen.
- Avoid clever one-liners when a straightforward form is clearer; optimize only when measured or clearly on a hot path.

## Examples

```cpp
// ❌ Noise: repeats what the line already says
// Increment i by 1
i++;

// ✅ Teaches context
// Advance to the next tile in row-major order; width is fixed for this layer.
i++;
```

